Advent of Code workspace

## Structure
- aoc/            Python package with solutions + runner
- aoc/years/      Year packages (e.g. aoc/years/y2025/day01.py)
- aoc/utils.py    Common helper functions for AoC puzzles
- inputs/         Your puzzle inputs (ignored by git)
- scripts/        Small helper scripts
- tests/          stdlib unittest tests

## Usage

### Create a new day scaffold
Creates day module, input file, and test file:
```bash
python scripts/aoc_new.py 2025 2
```

### Run solutions
Run both parts (default):
```bash
python -m aoc 2025 1
```

Run a specific part:
```bash
python -m aoc 2025 1 --part 1
python -m aoc 2025 1 --part 2
```

Show execution time:
```bash
python -m aoc 2025 1 --time
```

Use custom input file:
```bash
python -m aoc 2025 1 --input path/to/input.txt
```

Read from stdin:
```bash
cat some_input.txt | python -m aoc 2025 1 --input -
```

### Run tests
```bash
python -m unittest discover -s tests
```

## Utility Functions

The `aoc.utils` module provides common helpers:
- `lines(text)` - Split into non-empty lines
- `ints(text)` - Parse one integer per line
- `extract_ints(text)` - Extract all integers from text using regex
- `chunks(text)` - Split on blank lines
- `sliding_window(seq, n)` - Generate sliding windows
- `grid(text)` - Parse text into 2D grid
- `neighbors_4(row, col)` - Get 4-directional neighbors
- `neighbors_8(row, col)` - Get 8-directional neighbors (including diagonals)
- `in_bounds(grid, row, col)` - Check if position is in bounds
- `manhattan_distance(pos1, pos2)` - Calculate Manhattan distance
